<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c5bcec4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2331"><num value="2331">§ 2331.</num><heading> Use of continuing contracts for construction of certain projects</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6c5bcec5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2331/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the Secretary shall not implement a fully allocated funding policy with respect to a water resource project if initiation of construction has occurred but sufficient funds are not available to complete the project.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6c5bcec6-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2331/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Continuing contracts</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall enter into a continuing contract for a project described in subsection (a).</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6c5bcec7-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2331/c"><num value="c" class="bold">(c)</num><heading class="bold"> Initiation of construction clarified</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purposes of this section, initiation of construction for a project occurs on the date of enactment of an Act that appropriates funds for the project from 1 of the following appropriation accounts:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6c5bcec8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2331/c/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> Construction, General.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6c5bcec9-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2331/c/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> Operation and Maintenance, General.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6c5bceca-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2331/c/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> Flood Control, Mississippi River and Tributaries.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id6c5bcecb-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/53/tII/s206">Pub. L. 106–53, title II, § 206</ref>, <date date="1999-08-17">Aug. 17, 1999</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/113/286">113 Stat. 286</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6c5bcecc-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6c5bcecd-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id6c5bcece-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was enacted as part of the Water Resources Development Act of 1999, and not as part of the Water Resources Development Act of 1986 which comprises this chapter.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id6c5bcecf-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I87" topic="miscellaneous" id="id6c5bced0-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">“Secretary” Defined</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Secretary means the Secretary of the Army, see <ref href="/us/pl/106/53/s2">section 2 of Pub. L. 106–53</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s2201">section 2201 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
